text: Hiwannee is an unincorporated community in Wayne County, in the U.S. state of Mississippi. ==History== A post office called Hiwannee was established in 1901, and remained in operation until 1973. Hiwannee is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "fruit-destroying insect". Variant transliterations are "Hewhannee" and "Hiyoowanne". ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Mississippi Category:Unincorporated communities in Wayne County, Mississippi
title: Hiwannee, Mississippi
